  "title": "Global Plant Functional Trait Maps at 1 km Resolution",
  "description": "This dataset provides 31 global plant functional trait maps at 1 km spatial resolution. The maps represent community-weighted mean trait values and were generated by combining crowdsourced biodiversity observations, vegetation survey data, and in situ plant trait measurements with Earth observation-derived environmental variables. Input data include species occurrence records from GBIF, vegetation surveys from sPlot, trait measurements from the TRY database, and environmental predictors derived from satellite observations and global datasets, including surface reflectance, climate, soil properties, canopy height, and vegetation optical depth. The resulting maps offer globally consistent estimates of plant functional composition and can support ecological research, biodiversity assessments, and Earth system modeling applications.",
